      <h1 class="font-display text-5xl sm:text-6xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide uppercase leading-tight mb-8">
        Roller Conveyors: Types, Applications &#x26; Specifications
      </h1>
      <div class="text-xl text-ink-muted leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        <p>A roller conveyor uses a series of cylindrical rollers mounted between side frames to transport flat-bottomed products such as cases, cartons, totes, and pallets. Roller conveyors come in five primary types: gravity (unpowered), belt-driven live roller (BDLR), line-shaft, motor driven roller (MDR), and chain driven live roller (CDLR). They are the most widely installed conveyor category in packaging and distribution facilities worldwide.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Sub-type Navigation -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-surface" aria-labelledby="subtypes-heading">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
