  <!-- Applications -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim bg-dots" aria-labelledby="applications-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Applications</div>
      <h2 id="applications-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        Roller Conveyor <span class="text-accent">Applications</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">Case and Carton Transport</h3>
        <p>Roller conveyors dominate case transport in <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">packaging line applications</a>. Sealed cases with flat bottoms ride smoothly across rollers at speeds from 30 to 200 FPM. End-of-line systems typically use <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/powered/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">powered roller conveyors</a> between case packers, case sealers, labelers, and palletizers. <a href="/conveyor-types/accumulation-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Accumulation zones</a> buffer cases before palletizing.</p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">Distribution and Fulfillment</h3>
        <p>Distribution centers use <a href="/conveyor-types/mdr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">MDR roller conveyors</a> for zone-controlled transport and accumulation. Totes and shipping cartons route through pick modules, merge onto trunk lines, and accumulate before shipping sorters. MDR provides silent zero-pressure accumulation that protects product and reduces energy consumption. Intelligrated (Honeywell), Dematic, and TGW integrate MDR roller conveyors into large-scale <a href="/resources/automated-conveyor-systems/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">automated conveyor systems</a>.</p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">Pallet Handling</h3>
        <p><a href="/conveyor-types/cdlr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">CDLR conveyors</a> handle loaded pallets between stretch wrappers, pallet jacks, and truck loading areas. Heavy-duty rollers with 3.5" diameter and 7-gauge wall thickness support pallet loads up to 4,000 lbs on standard frames and 10,000+ lbs on structural frames. <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/pallet/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Pallet conveyor systems</a> often include <a href="/conveyor-types/transfer-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">right-angle transfers</a> and <a href="/conveyor-types/vertical-reciprocating/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">vertical reciprocating conveyors</a> for multi-level facilities.</p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">Food and Beverage</h3>
        <p><a href="/industries/food-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Food and beverage facilities</a> use stainless steel roller conveyors with sealed bearings and open-frame construction for washdown cleaning. <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/sanitary/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Sanitary roller conveyors</a> feature tool-free roller removal, sloped frame surfaces that shed water, and FDA-compliant bearing seals. Dorner and mk North America manufacture purpose-built sanitary roller conveyor lines.</p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink">Loading Docks and Shipping</h3>
        <p><a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/gravity/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Gravity roller conveyors</a> are the standard for loading dock applications. Workers push cases down a slight decline into trailers. Flexible/expandable gravity roller sections telescope to reach deep into trailers. These cost a fraction of powered systems and require zero electrical infrastructure.</p>
      </div>
