  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide mb-10">
        Frequently Asked <span class="text-accent">Questions</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8" open>
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What are the different types of roller conveyors?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>The five main roller conveyor types are: <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/gravity/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">gravity roller</a> (unpowered), belt-driven live roller or BDLR (single motor drives all rollers via belt), line-shaft roller (motor drives rollers via splined shaft and O-rings), <a href="/conveyor-types/mdr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">MDR</a> (24VDC motors inside individual rollers), and <a href="/conveyor-types/cdlr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">CDLR</a> (chain loops drive rollers via sprockets for heavy loads).</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How do I choose between gravity and powered roller conveyors?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Choose <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/gravity/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">gravity roller</a> when you have a slight decline (3-5 degrees), consistent product weights, and no need for speed control or <a href="/conveyor-types/accumulation-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">accumulation</a>. Choose <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/powered/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">powered roller</a> when you need consistent speed, uphill transport, accumulation, or integration with <a href="/resources/automated-conveyor-systems/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">automated systems</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What roller spacing do I need?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>At least 3 rollers must contact the product bottom at all times. Divide your smallest product length by 3, then round down to the nearest standard pitch (1.5", 2", 3", 4.5", or 6"). A 12-inch long case needs 4-inch or smaller roller spacing. A 24-inch pallet needs 8-inch or smaller spacing.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is the weight capacity of a roller conveyor?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Weight capacity depends on roller type. Standard gravity rollers: 75-200 lbs per product. BDLR: up to 500 lbs. <a href="/conveyor-types/mdr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">MDR</a>: 150-250 lbs per zone. <a href="/conveyor-types/cdlr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">CDLR</a>: 500-10,000+ lbs for <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/pallet/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">pallet applications</a>. Capacity depends on roller diameter, wall thickness, bearing type, and frame gauge.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            Why is MDR replacing line-shaft conveyors?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p><a href="/conveyor-types/mdr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">MDR technology</a> provides zero-pressure accumulation without pneumatics, uses 50%+ less energy (zones only run when needed), runs quieter (65 dB vs 80+ dB), requires less maintenance (no belts, chains, or O-rings), and supports easy zone-by-zone expansion. Interroll, Itoh Denki, and Rulmeca are leading MDR roller manufacturers.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
